nd","Thame, Oxfordshire, England":"Thame, Oxfordshire, England","Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England":"Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England","Adderbury, Oxfordshire, England":"Adderbury, Oxfordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Babcock","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Lancashire): although the first element of this name would suggest it is derived from the Middle English personal name <i>Babb</i> (see   Babb  ), apparently it is a post-medieval form of <b>Badcock</b>, from the Middle English personal name <i>Badecok</i>, a pet form of <i>Bade</i> (see   Bade  ) + the diminutive suffix <i>-cok</i>. There is no reason why a Middle English <i>Babbecok</i>, a pet form of <i>Babb</i> (itself a pet form of   Barbara  ), should not have existed, but evidence has yet to be found.","History: James Babcock settled in Portsmouth, RI, in 1642."],"variants":[{"name":"Babb","meanings":["English (Devon, Somerset, and Cornwall): from the Middle English personal name <i>Babb(e)</i>, usually no doubt a pet form of the female personal name <i>Barbara</i> (see   Barbara  ), but possibly in some cases a survival of the Old English personal name <i>Babba</i>, which is found in several placenames, including Babbacombe in Devon and Babington in Somerset.","English (Devon, Somerset, and Cornwall): from Middle English <i>babe</i> ‘infant, young child’, applied as a nickname.","Americanized form of German   Bobb   or of some other similar (like-sounding) surname."]}]},{"name":"Polly","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant of   Molly  , established as an independent given name since the 18th century. The reason for the interchange of <i>M-</i> and <i>P-</i> is not clear;  compare  Peg ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":22,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Polly Babcock was born in 1360, in Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, her father, Robert Babcock, was 25 and her mother, Mrs. Sir Robert Babcock, was 22. She married Robert Badlington. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1440, in Adderbury, Oxfordshire, England, at the age of 80."},"et":{"1360–1440":"1360–1440","1357–1430":"1357–1430","1387–1430":"1387–1430","1335–Male":"1335–Surnud","1339–Female":"1339–Surnud","1335":"1335","1357":"1357","1387":"1387","1430":"1430","1440":"1440","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","1339":"1339","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England","Thame, Oxfordshire, England":"Thame, Oxfordshire, England","Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England":"Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England","Adderbury, Oxfordshire, England":"Adderbury, Oxfordshire, England"},"fi":{"1360–1440":"1360–1440","1357–1430":"1357–1430","1387–1430":"1387–1430","1335–Male":"1335–Kuollut","1339–Female":"1339–Kuollut","1335":"1335","1357":"1357","1387":"1387","1430":"1430","1440":"1440","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","1339":"1339","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England","Thame, Oxfordshire, England":"Thame, Oxfordshire, England","Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England":"Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England","Adderbury, Oxfordshire, England":"Adderbury, Oxfordshire, England"},"fr":{"1360–1440":"1360–1440","1357–1430":"1357–1430","1387–1430":"1387–1430","1335–Male":"1335–Décédé","1339–Female":"1339–Décédée","1335":"1335","1357":"1357","1387":"1387","1430":"1430","1440":"1440","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","1339":"1339","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, Angleter